<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="146" pageId="6" pageNumber="145" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,1643,2065]" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Robinson" authorityYear="1999" baseAuthorityName="Cabrera" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[189,445,1643,1669]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Mesanthophora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="145" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rojasii">
<emphasis box="[189,445,1643,1669]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">Mesanthophora rojasii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in the Chaco region in 
<collectingCountry box="[787,869,1643,1669]" name="Bolivia" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
(department of 
<collectingRegion box="[1048,1175,1643,1669]" country="Bolivia" name="Santa Cruz" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">Santa Cruz</collectingRegion>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[1194,1298,1643,1669]" name="Paraguay" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
(departments of 
<collectingRegion box="[167,330,1679,1705]" country="Paraguay" name="Alto Paraguay" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">Alto Paraguay</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[343,477,1679,1705]" country="Paraguay" name="Concepcion" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">Concepción</collectingRegion>
and Central), as well as in 
<collectingCountry box="[794,865,1679,1705]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, in the Pantanal region of the state of 
<collectingRegion country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso do Sul" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">Mato Grosso do Sul</collectingRegion>
and now, for the first time, reported in the Caatinga domain, in northern 
<collectingRegion box="[1033,1183,1715,1741]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation box="[1199,1267,1715,1741]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[136,229,1538,1560]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,609,1514]" captionTargetId="figure-198@6.[151,1436,605,1514]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Geographic distribution of Mesanthophora rojasii, including the new record in the state of Minas Gerais." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5556307" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5556307/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Cabrera, A. L." box="[1290,1447,1715,1741]" pageId="6" pageNumber="145" pagination="133 - 140" refId="ref4465" refString="Cabrera, A. L. (1940) Cuatro compuestas nuevas de la America Austral. Darwiniana 4: 133 - 140." type="journal article" year="1940">Cabrera 1940</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Cabrera, A. L. &amp; Dematteis, M." box="[136,439,1751,1777]" pageId="6" pageNumber="145" pagination="65 - 268" refId="ref4489" refString="Cabrera, A. L. &amp; Dematteis, M. (2009) Vernonieae. In: Cabrera, A. L., Dematteis, M. &amp; Freire, S. E. (Vol. Orgs). Compositae VI. Ramella, L. &amp; Perret, P. (series eds.), Flora del Paraguay fasc. 39., Conservatoire et Jardin Botanique de la Ville de Geneve, Geneva, pp 65 - 268." type="book chapter" year="2009">Cabrera &amp; Dematteis 2009</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hind, D. J. N." box="[450,571,1751,1777]" pageId="6" pageNumber="145" refId="ref5075" refString="Hind, D. J. N. (2011) An annotated preliminary checklist of the Compositae of Bolivia. Version 2." type="book" year="2011">Hind 2011</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Roque, N. &amp; Teles, A. M. &amp; Moura, L. &amp; Pacheco, R. A. &amp; Silva, G. H. L. &amp; Alves, M. &amp; Nakajima, J. N." box="[582,786,1751,1777]" pageId="6" pageNumber="145" pagination="147 - 156" refId="ref6613" refString="Roque, N., Teles, A. M., Moura, L., Pacheco, R. A., Silva, G. H. L., Alves, M. &amp; Nakajima, J. N. (2018) Check-list de Asteraceae no estado de Mato Grosso do Sul, Brasil. Iheringia serie botanica 73 (supl.): 147 - 156. https: // doi. org / 10.21826 / 2446 - 8231201873 s 147" type="journal article" year="2018">
Roque 
<emphasis box="[662,711,1751,1777]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
). This species occurs over limestone outcrops in xerophytic vegetation (savannah, caatinga) or in 
<emphasis box="[553,679,1787,1813]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">carandazal</emphasis>
(annually flooded vegetation composed of a native palm, 
<taxonomicName authority="Morong" authorityName="Morong" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Copernicia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="6" pageNumber="145" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">Copernicia alba</emphasis>
Morong
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Morong, T. &amp; Britton, N. L." box="[313,661,1823,1850]" pageId="6" pageNumber="145" pagination="45 - 637" refId="ref6002" refString="Morong, T. &amp; Britton, N. L. (1893) An Enumeration of the Plants Collected by Dr. Thomas Morong in Paraguay. Annals of the New York Academy Science 7: 45 - 637. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1749 - 6632.1893. tb 55410. x" type="journal article" year="1893">Morong &amp; Britton (1893: 246))</bibRefCitation>
, the latter being closely associated with accumulation of sub-superficial carbonaceous concretions (
<bibRefCitation author="Silva, M. P. &amp; Mauro, R. &amp; Mourao, G. &amp; Coutinho, M." box="[443,638,1859,1885]" pageId="6" pageNumber="145" pagination="143 - 152" refId="ref7268" refString="Silva, M. P. Mauro, R., Mourao, G. &amp; Coutinho, M. (2000) Distribuicao e quantificacao de classes de vegetacao do Pantanal atraves de levantamento aereo. Revista Brasileira de Botanica 23: 143 - 152. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0100 - 84042000000200004" type="journal article" year="2000">
Silva 
<emphasis box="[510,568,1859,1885]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">et al.</emphasis>
2000
</bibRefCitation>
). The notable new record in northern 
<collectingRegion box="[1070,1222,1859,1885]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
(ca. 
<quantity box="[1281,1388,1859,1886]" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="145" unit="km" value="1500.0">1,500 km</quantity>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[136,370,1895,1922]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso do Sul" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">Mato Grosso do Sul</collectingRegion>
) might be explained by the presence of similar limestone outcrops (
<bibRefCitation author="Oliveira, C. V. &amp; Ker, J. C. &amp; Duarte, M. N. &amp; Curi, N. &amp; Fontes, L. E. F." box="[1156,1385,1895,1921]" pageId="6" pageNumber="145" pagination="117 - 128" refId="ref6113" refString="Oliveira, C. V., Ker, J. C., Duarte, M. N., Curi, N. &amp; Fontes, L. E. F. (2000) Atributos micromorfologicos de solos do projeto Jaiba, Norte de Minas Gerais. Revista Brasileira de Ciencias do Solo 24: 117 - 128. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0100 - 06832000000100014" type="journal article" year="2000">
Oliveira 
<emphasis box="[1259,1318,1895,1921]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">et al.</emphasis>
2000
</bibRefCitation>
) with xerophytic vegetation in both regions (
<bibRefCitation author="Rizzini, C. T." box="[563,708,1931,1957]" pageId="6" pageNumber="145" refId="ref6344" refString="Rizzini, C. T. (1997) Tratado de Fitogeografia do Brasil. Aspectos ecologicos, sociologicos e floristicos. Ed. 2. Rio de Janeiro, Ambito Cultural. 747 pp." type="book" year="1997">Rizzini 1997</bibRefCitation>
) and shows its likely adaptation to Seasonally Dry Forests in South America.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,1643,2065]" lastBlockId="7.[136,1452,158,545]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="146" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">
During our study of herbarium collections, we came across a single specimen from 
<collectingRegion box="[1138,1291,2003,2029]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, which makes the information provided on the voucher label doubtful, as it is an older collection (dated 1984) from a location with different environmental characteristics than those preferred by the species. To confirm its validity, we compared this voucher’s locality with other collections made by M.C.B. Teixeira &amp; Carvalho on the same date and location. The voucher is one of many collections made by the collectors (especially M.C.B Teixeira) in the municipality of Jaíba between the years 1982 and 1984. The species identity remained undetermined at the time of collection. Based on this finding, we consider the location stated in the label to be correct and assume that the species was truly collected in 
<collectingRegion box="[136,290,338,364]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="146" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,158,545]" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">
This is the third species of Mesanthophorinae recorded in the Caatinga domain, together with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Mart. ex Candolle 1836: 60) Robinson (1989: 291)" authorityName="Robinson" authorityPageNumber="291" authorityYear="1989" baseAuthorityName="Candolle" baseAuthorityPageNumber="60" baseAuthorityYear="1836" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Acilepidopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="echitifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">Acilepidopsis echitifolia</emphasis>
(Mart. ex 
<bibRefCitation author="Candolle, A. P. de" box="[369,577,410,437]" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" refId="ref4574" refString="Candolle, A. P. de (1836) Prodromus Systematis Naturalis Regni Vegetabilis, vol. 5. Treutel &amp; Wurtz, Paris, 706 pp." type="book" year="1836">Candolle 1836: 60</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Robinson, H." box="[593,842,410,436]" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" pagination="289 - 292" refId="ref6380" refString="Robinson, H. (1989) Acilepdopsis, a new genus of Vernonieae from South America (Asteraceae). Phytologia 67: 289 - 292." type="journal article" year="1989">Robinson (1989: 291)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, in the state of 
<collectingRegion box="[1014,1082,410,436]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Mart. ex Baker (1873: 170)" authorityName="Baker" authorityPageNumber="170" authorityYear="1873" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Telmatophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scolymastrum">
<emphasis box="[1142,1452,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">Telmatophila scolymastrum</emphasis>
Mart. ex 
<bibRefCitation author="Baker, J. G." box="[237,443,446,472]" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" pagination="5 - 180" refId="ref4369" refString="Baker, J. G. (1873) Compositae I. Vernoniaceae. In: Martius †, C. F. P. von &amp; Eichler, A. W. (Eds.) Flora brasiliensis, vol. 6 (2). F. Fleischer, Munich, Vienna &amp; Leipzig, pp. 5 - 180." type="book chapter" year="1873">Baker (1873: 170)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, endemic to caatinga vegetation in the state of 
<collectingRegion box="[964,1022,446,472]" country="Brazil" name="Piaui" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">Piauí</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Nakajima, J." box="[1035,1211,446,472]" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" pagination="2020" refId="ref6062" refString="Nakajima, J. (2020) Telmatophila. In: Flora do Brasil 2020. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / reflora / floradobrasil / FB 163 - 44 (accessed 30 March 2021)" type="book chapter" year="2020">Nakajima 2020</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Picanco, W. L. &amp; Loeuille, B. F. P. &amp; Marques, D. &amp; Nakajima, J. &amp; Souza-Souza, R. M. B. &amp; Esteves, R. L." box="[1222,1440,446,473]" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" pagination="2020" refId="ref6188" refString="Picanco, W. L., Loeuille, B. F. P., Marques, D., Nakajima, J., Souza-Souza, R. M. B. &amp; Esteves, R. L. (2020) Acilepidopsis. In: Flora do Brasil 2020. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro." type="book chapter" year="2020">
Picanço 
<emphasis box="[1317,1366,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">et al</emphasis>
. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
). These monotypic genera differ mainly by characteristics of the leaves, capitulescence, position of the capitula and number of florets per capitulum (
<bibRefCitation author="Baker, J. G." box="[507,641,518,544]" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" pagination="5 - 180" refId="ref4369" refString="Baker, J. G. (1873) Compositae I. Vernoniaceae. In: Martius †, C. F. P. von &amp; Eichler, A. W. (Eds.) Flora brasiliensis, vol. 6 (2). F. Fleischer, Munich, Vienna &amp; Leipzig, pp. 5 - 180." type="book chapter" year="1873">Baker 1873</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Robinson, H." box="[652,826,518,544]" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" pagination="289 - 292" refId="ref6380" refString="Robinson, H. (1989) Acilepdopsis, a new genus of Vernonieae from South America (Asteraceae). Phytologia 67: 289 - 292." type="journal article" year="1989">Robinson 1989</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Robinson, H." box="[837,1026,518,545]" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" pagination="169 - 172" refId="ref6447" refString="Robinson, H. (1992 b) Mesanthophora, a new genus of Vernonieae (Asteraceae) from Paraguay. Novon 2: 169 - 172. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3391681" type="journal article" year="1992">Robinson 1992b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
